2022-11-12@23:01:23.000-05:00
The vim sudo trick allows you to write to file that requires root permissions for writing.
You can enter `w !sudo tee %` to write the actual without having to close, lose changes, and reopen.
Additionally, you can add the following to your `.vimrc` to provide a shorter and easier to remember alternative:
`cmap w!! w !sudo tee > /dev/null %`

2022-11-16@21:19:45.000-05:00
You can use a [target='_blank'] CSS selector to identify external links (if you make all external links open in new tabs).
Then, you can add a ::after { content } rule in order to signify these as external! 